originalText.text: Rachel was our wedding and engagement photographer. My husband and I were honestly blown away... not just for the quality of her photos and her ability to capture the most beautiful moments for us, but also for her beautiful spirit and positive energy on our day! We both felt a little awkward in front of a camera at first but Rachel gave us a little direction and a lot of encouragement that led to fabulous photos of us, our families and wedding guests. No one tells you how important it is to surround yourself with vendor-partners who give you good vibes on your wedding day. It's obvious in retrospect, because you spend so much time on such an important day with these folks, but take it from us: it cannot be underrated. Rachel was not only so professional and on top of it, but she was also a joy to be around. She's extremely diligent, and made sure to capture all the photos we specifically wanted, even going so far as to find us late in the night and snap pictures of us with my grandparents who didn't participate in the original family photos. Without her, I wouldn't have remembered to do that and would have missed out on that precious, precious memory. We spoke to several other photographers at different price-points. While Rachel ended up being one of the more expensive photographers, we chose her for her ability to capture candid, beautiful moments and honestly feel like she was worth every penny! We would absolutely choose her all over again. If you're lucky enough to book her, you will be so glad you did. Thank you, Rachel!

originalText.text: Rachel is absolutely incredible!!! She is by far the best photographer I have ever worked with. Rachel is extremely talented, creative, artistic, professional, passionate, warm, thoughtful, and such a joy to work with. She made sure I felt comfortable every step of the way, while still directing and guiding me as necessary to ensure she would capture the best possible photos. Rachel was also so wonderful with my dog and took the most adorable photos of her. Rachel also turned around the edited photos so quickly which was an added bonus. I am in awe of Rachel’s talent and ability to capture such beautiful moments, and absolutely adore every since photo I received. I am already planning to book another photo shoot with Rachel because of how amazing she made this experience. I cannot recommend Rachel highly enough—if you hire Rachel, you will not regret it!

originalText.text: Rachel was absolutely one of the BEST people we booked for our wedding day. My husband and I are wedding photographers ourselves, so of course we were extremely picky about who we wanted to work with. After researching an insane amount, we found Rachel and are so grateful we did. She has such a passion for what she does, and really brings her endless creativity and energy into everything. It was also super important to us that we booked someone who could capture us having fun, laughing, and just letting us be ourselves. She did all that and so much more, making us super comfortable while still guiding us to create the best photos possible. Our engagement photos were stunning and our wedding photos are even better. All those special moments and people were captured, and we’ll have the photos to enjoy for the rest of our lives. We can’t thank Rachel enough!!

originalText.text: Words cannot express how happy we were with hiring Rachel to be our wedding photographer! To me, the photography was one of the most important parts of our wedding. As the bride I knew that the day would be a blur and I was looking for someone to really capture the life and emotions of the day so that I could look back and really take it all in over and over again.  Rachel did just that and more.  She clearly has her own style, not cookie cutter and traditional, she’s creative, artistic and really just nailed capturing so many special moments. So many guests saw the photos and were blown away by them, and how they expressed such love and emotion.  Rachel as a person is also a joy to work with, less of a vendor and more of a friend which makes you feel so comfortable.  She’s professional, super knowledgeable and you can really tell that this is her passion as she is a true artist. She made my husband and I feel confident which I’m sure helped with capturing the portraits etc.  What really wowed me were the numerous mediums she used in her photography, the vintage camera was one of my favorites! Not to mention how flexible she was when we had to reschedule our original date due to COVID. I really can’t recommend her enough, and will continue to do so! Thanks for killing it Rachel!

originalText.text: Rachel was truly amazing to work with! She shot our engagement shoot, our rehearsal dinner, and our wedding and I couldn’t be happier! She is easy to work with, and takes the most elegant, classic, timeless photos. She has an artistic eye and consistently delivers! One picture is better than the next. She knew exactly when we needed a break, when we needed some direction, and we felt like she was always in the background so we could enjoy our day! Her young, fun, energetic personality added to the magic of the day! She has such a quick turn around, and her photos show how passionate she is about her profession. She was timely in regards to her communication, always making us feel at ease. She was able to answer all of our questions along the way and was beyond flexible. The wedding party kept commenting how smooth the day was because of Rachel! Highly recommend! You will not be disappointed!
